In [117]:
#['brand_name']: The brand or manufacturer of the phone.
#['price']: The price of the phone in a certain currency.
#['rating']: The rating of the phone out of 100.
#['has_5g']: Indicates whether the phone supports 5G connectivity (True or False).
#['has_nfc']: Indicates whether the phone supports NFC (Near Field Communication) technology (True or False).
#['has_ir_blaster']: Indicates whether the phone has an infrared (IR) blaster (True or False).
#['processor_brand']: The brand of the phone's processor (e.g., Snapdragon, Exynos, Dimensity).
#['num_cores']: The number of cores in the phone's processor.
#['processor_speed']: The speed of the processor in GHz.
#['battery_capacity']: The battery capacity of the phone in mAh (milliampere-hours).
#['fast_charging_available']: Indicates whether the phone supports fast charging (True or False).
#['fast_charging']: The speed of fast charging in watts (if applicable).
#['ram_capacity']: The amount of RAM in the phone in GB.
#['internal_memory']: The internal storage capacity of the phone in GB.
#['screen_size']: The size of the phone's display in inches.
#['refresh_rate']: The refresh rate of the phone's display in Hz.
#['num_rear_cameras']: The number of cameras on the back of the phone.
#['num_front_cameras']: The number of cameras on the front of the phone.
#['os']: The operating system the phone uses (e.g., Android).
#['primary_camera_rear']: The resolution of the primary rear camera in megapixels.
#['primary_camera_front']: The resolution of the primary front camera in megapixels.
#['extended_memory_available']: Indicates whether the phone supports extended memory via an external memory card (True or False).
#['extended_upto']: The maximum amount of extended memory supported by the phone in GB.
#['resolution_width']: The width of the phone's display resolution in pixels.
#['resolution_height']: The height of the phone's display resolution in pixels.

columns_to_drop = ['has_ir_blaster', 'num_cores', 'num_front_cameras', 'num_rear_cameras', 
                    'extended_memory_available', 'extended_upto', 'refresh_rate']
df = df.drop(columns=columns_to_drop)

['has_ir_blaster']: Infrared blasters are not common and might not significantly affect the phone's price.¶

['num_cores']: Since you have processor_speed, the number of cores might be less impactful. However, this could also depend on how significant the cores are to the price.¶

['num_front_cameras and num_rear_cameras']: The actual quality (megapixels) of cameras might be more important than the number of cameras.¶

['extended_memory_available and extended_upto']: These may not significantly impact the price if most phones have similar capacities.¶

['refresh_rate']: While important for display quality, it may not significantly impact the price compared to other features like screen size and resolution.¶

HANDLING MISSING VALUES

In [136]:
# Filling missing values for numerical columns with mean/median
df['rating'] = df['rating'].fillna(df['rating'].mean())
df['processor_speed'] = df['processor_speed'].fillna(df['processor_speed'].mean())
df['battery_capacity'] = df['battery_capacity'].fillna(df['battery_capacity'].median())
df['primary_camera_front'] = df['primary_camera_front'].fillna(df['primary_camera_front'].median())

# Filling missing values for categorical columns with mode
df['processor_brand'] = df['processor_brand'].fillna(df['processor_brand'].mode()[0])
df['os'] = df['os'].fillna(df['os'].mode()[0])

# Handle null values in fast_charging column
df['fast_charging'].fillna(0, inplace=True)  # Replace nulls with 0, assuming no fast charging

# Checking redundancy
redundant = ((df['fast_charging_available'] == (df['fast_charging'] > 0)).all())

# If redundant, drop the fast_charging_available column
if redundant:
    df = df.drop(columns=['fast_charging_available'])

# To Verify no missing values 
print(df.isnull().sum())
